	<meta property="og:description" content="For almost a year now, Brandon and I have performed a particular ritual at the start of each new season. It’s going to make some of you want to roll your eyes and gag &#8211; and really, be my guest; I gag a little just typing this &#8211; but I want to tell you about it anyway, because it’s kind of dreamy. You might even want to join in. Basically, the ritual goes like this: one night, when the season is just beginning, we climb into bed, prop ourselves up on pillows, and I read to him from Edna Lewis’s The Taste of Country Cooking. Now, I know what you’re thinking: You read aloud to him? From a cookbook? Oh,&hellip;" />
