      <p>Gasp, you&#8217;ve never creamed butter by hand? But that is, in my opinion, the best part about baking. The intrinsic feeling of having the butter change textures under your hands, the way it lightens in texture as the sugar is incorporated, that&#8217;s the hows and whys of cake making. Maybe I&#8217;m just a luddite, but I love to do it by hand.</></>This sounds exactly like something I&#8217;d love, and while I know it stands alone as a plain cake, I bet you could play around with adding a few anise seeds, or some vanilla  bean or lemon or (ooooh) black pepper and serve it with fresh peaches.</p>
