    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://profile.typekey.com/megrje/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">megrje</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/02/like-a-lullaby/#comment-8763"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-02-12T12:58:00-05:00">Tuesday, February 12, 2008 at 12:58 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have to say- I don&#8217;t have a stand mixer, and I don&#8217;t always like to pull out the hand mixer, so I frequently just do it by hand. (Although people give me the look of the crazy for meringue and whipped cream). But for cakes I think it&#8217;s great because you don&#8217;t want to overmix them and you can see exactly when everything is blended. It really doesn&#8217;t take that much longer, you just have to start with softened butter.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-8763' data-commentid="8763" data-postid="1320" data-belowelement="comment-8763" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to megrje" aria-label='Reply to megrje'>Reply</a>    </div>
