      <p>I think that it is perfectly normal to do stuff like that. My husband and I have a game we play where we give each other a cooking scenario and the other has to come up with a solution. For example: &#8216;casual meal for six  &#8211; seasonal ingredients, you have to buy everything in a 5 mile radius&#8217; or &#8216; meal for two, has to include beef and    chocolate&#8217;. Okay, I sound quite weird now &#8211; but it&#8217;s a great way to make up after a row. !!?!!</p>
