      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/02/like-a-lullaby/#comment-8829"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-01-30T03:17:00-05:00">Friday, January 30, 2009 at 3:17 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, </>I know I&#8217;ve already commented on this recipe, but I just <>had<> to tell you &#8211; with no idea what to bake for my birthday, and no one else to do the baking for me, I turned to this recipe. </>Just a simple, one layer cake. I rubbed lemon zest into the sugar before combining it with the butter. When it was done baking and cooling, I sliced it in half to make two layers. I smoothed a lemon almond buttercream icing in the middle, topped by a thin layer of homemade blueberry sauce. I iced the top with the buttercream, then right before serving it, I heated up the blueberry sauce and poured it on top. </>It was perfect. </>And all my guests were so pleased. </>Thank you.</p>
    </div>

